f=Engineering/dev/operational/agent/dev-config.md · p=Machine-readable configuration dev, department's law layer. · h2:Config Template=`# --- Core documents --- \· stack_profile_path: <FILL_IN>        # the per-business stack document (from the template) \· adr_ledger_path: <FILL_IN>           # append-only ADR ledger \· security_charter_path: <FILL_IN>     # the operator-adopted Security Charter (senior authority) \· ` · in=`stack_profile_path` build before non-trivial work; provisional labeling meanwhile. `security_charter_path` (unadopted) department runs charter's most-restrictive reading (no external tools, writes, red-team), stated affected output. Domain reviewers fixed department roster; ADRs/PRs touching domain get agent's review before logging/merge. · f=Unfilled config degrades loudly, never silently. charter's absence loudest degradation.